Paper: hep-th/9609218

Date: 1996-09-27

Title: Action Principle for the Classical Dual Electrodynamics

Authors: P.C.R. Cardoso de Mello, S. Carneiro and M.C. Nemes

Comments: latex, 8 pages, no figures

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B384 (1996) 197-200

The purpose of this paper is to formulate an action principle which allowsfor the construction of a classical lagrangean including both electric andmagnetic currents. The lagrangean is non-local and shown to yield all theexpected (local) equations for dual electrodynamics.